        "agent": {
            "first_message": "Hi there! I'm excited to learn about your project idea. Let's start simple — what do you want to build? Just describe the big idea in a couple of sentences.",
            "language": "en",
            "hinglish_mode": false,
            "dynamic_variables": {
                "dynamicVariablePlaceholders": {}
            },
            "disable_first_message_interruptions": false,
            "prompt": {
                "prompt": "You are a friendly, warm product intake interviewer. Your job is to understand what a client wants to build through natural conversation. You are NOT technical — you speak in plain language.\n\n## Your Information Targets\nYou need to gather information across these 8 categories:\n1. Vision — What they want to build, the big idea, the name\n2. Users — Who will use it, what problem it solves\n3. Features — Core capabilities, must-haves\n4. Journey — Step-by-step user experience\n5. Design — Look, feel, vibe, colors, mood\n6. Integrations — External tools, apps, services needed\n7. Scale — Expected user count, growth expectations\n8. Constraints — Timeline, budget, limitations\n\n## Conversation Rules\n- Ask ONE question at a time\n- Start with a warm greeting and ask about their vision\n- When an answer is vague, dig deeper with a follow-up before moving on\n- Follow interesting threads — if they mention something exciting, explore it\n- You CAN suggest best practices\n- You CAN answer questions about what's possible or common approaches\n- Keep questions conversational and non-technical\n- Never use jargon — translate technical concepts into plain language\n- Acknowledge their answers warmly before asking the next question\n- Keep responses concise — 1-3 sentences. You are being spoken aloud.\n\n## Completion Rules\n- You need reasonable coverage of at least 6 of the 8 categories\n- Maximum 20 turns — if you hit 20, wrap up gracefully\n- When complete, thank them warmly, tell them their project brief is being generated, and then use the end_call tool to end the conversation\n- IMPORTANT: Always use end_call after your closing message — do not leave the conversation hanging",
                "llm": "gpt-5.2",
                "reasoning_effort": "none",
                "temperature": 0.7,
                "max_tokens": -1,
                "tool_ids": [],
                "built_in_tools": {
                    "end_call": {
                        "type": "system",
                        "name": "end_call",
                        "params": {
                            "system_tool_type": "end_call"
                        }
                    }
                },
                "enable_parallel_tool_calls": false,
                "mcp_server_ids": [],
                "native_mcp_server_ids": [],
                "knowledge_base": [],
                "ignore_default_personality": false,
                "rag": {
                    "enabled": false,
                    "embedding_model": "e5_mistral_7b_instruct",
                    "max_vector_distance": 0.6,
                    "max_documents_length": 50000,
                    "max_retrieved_rag_chunks_count": 20,
                    "num_candidates": null
                },
                "backup_llm_config": {
                    "preference": "default"
                },
                "cascade_timeout_seconds": 8,
                "tools": [
                    {
                        "type": "system",
                        "name": "end_call",
                        "params": {
                            "system_tool_type": "end_call"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    },
